      • setParticipant

        public void setParticipant(URI participant)
                    throws SBOLValidationException
        Sets the participant property of this object to the given one.

        If this object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        participant -
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated SBOLDocument is not compliant.
        SBOLValidationException - if the given participant argument is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated ModuleDefinition instance is not null and given participant URI is not found in its list of FunctionalComponent instances.

        public boolean removeRole(URI roleURI)
                   throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes the given role reference from the set of role references.

        If this Participation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • clearRoles

        public void clearRoles()
                throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes all entries of this Participation object's set of role URIs. The set will be empty after this call returns.
